ZH: 我正在学习弹琴。
EN: I am learning to play the qin.

ZH: 昨天我修理了我的古琴。
EN: I repaired my guqin yesterday.

ZH: 爷爷传给我一把古琴。
EN: My grandfather passed down a guqin to me.

ZH: 我在音乐学院学习古琴。
EN: I am studying guqin at the music academy.

ZH: 她的琴声让人心旷神怡。
EN: Her qin playing is refreshing and pleasant.

ZH: 他是一位资深的琴师。
EN: He is a seasoned qin master.

ZH: 我在琴弦上涂了一层琴脂。
EN: I applied some qin wax on the strings.

ZH: 在古琴上拉弦有一定技巧。
EN: There is a certain technique to playing the strings of the guqin.

ZH: 他收藏了许多珍贵的古琴。
EN: He has collected many precious ancient qin.

ZH: 看到她拿着琴，我感到非常兴奋。
EN: I felt very excited when I saw her holding the qin.

ZH: 我在琴头上刻了花纹。
EN: I carved a pattern on the qin head.

ZH: 每次听到琴声，我都感到平静。
EN: I feel calm every time I hear the qin sound.

ZH: 他的琴艺已经达到了高超的境界。
EN: His qin skills have reached an advanced level.

ZH: 我把琴放在琴盒里。
EN: I put the qin in the qin case.

ZH: 这把琴的音质非常好。
EN: The sound quality of this qin is excellent.

ZH: 他喜欢用琴声来表达自己的情感。
EN: He likes to express his emotions through the sound of the qin.

ZH: 她在琴弦上轻轻一拨。
EN: She gently plucked the qin strings.

ZH: 我参加了古琴比赛。
EN: I participated in a guqin competition.

ZH: 春风轻轻吹拂着琴弦。
EN: The spring breeze gently rustles the qin strings.

ZH: 琴声如泉水般清澈。
EN: The qin sound is as clear as spring water.
